The paper deals with speech recognition and speaker diarization, which are both subfields of natural language processing (NLP) and signal processing. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.SD (Sound) are the most likely categories. The paper also utilizes recurrent neural networks, which are a popular tool in machine learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. The paper also involves modeling and optimization, which are common themes in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Signal Processing).
